Good morning,

This week=E2=80=99s Stratechery interview is with Michael Morton ( https://=
www.linkedin.com/in/michael-morton-98a1272b/ ). Morton is a senior research=
 analyst at MoffettNathanson ( https://www.moffettnathanson.com/ ) with a f=
ocus on e-commerce and marketplaces. Morton has worked on both the buy-side=
 and sale-side of equity analysis, and also worked on the YouTube strategy =
team prior to joining MoffettNathanson.

In this interview we discuss a few fascinating research notes Morton has wr=
itten recently: he=E2=80=99s very bullish on Shopify=E2=80=99s enterprise o=
ffering, even as he thinks that brands will end up on Amazon in the long ru=
n. We get into why he thinks both things are true, along with covering a ho=
st of other e-commerce topics: how COVID changed the structure of e-commerc=
e, Shopify Audiences, Amazon Buy With Prime and advertising businesses, and=
 why Walmart is poised to be the other big winner in the U.S.

